on 5/12/03 10:58, you related:
  
>> One had a cooling fan with allen head bolts (just like CV joint bolts) and
>> the other had 13mm head hex bolts. Which is original?
> 
> In the air-cooled Vanagon the cooling fan is held in place with hex bolts.

not only vanagon, also late bus, not positive, but aroundabout '76 model
year the fan changed slightly along with the hardware, from 8mm XZN screws
countersunk into the fan, to 8mm (13mm head) hex bolts sitting flat on the
fan center portion.

